user-5-0                      Xerox Quintus Prolog User's Guide                            Section 5-0: OverviewThis section gives a number of tips on how to organize your programs forincreased clarity.  See {manual(user-3-7)}, for additional style suggestionsthat can help you catch simple programming mistakes more easily.Because of its straightforward structure, Prolog is inherently more readablethan languages like Pascal and C. You can take full advantage of Prolog'sreadability by following the style conventions described below when you writeyour programs.